# Architecture Context

> Generated by kwidoo/hex-tools on {{ generated_at }}.
> Provides AI coding assistants with architectural context for this project.

## Architecture Rules

- Domain must not depend on Laravel, Eloquent, HTTP, Infrastructure, queues, jobs, controllers, resources, or external APIs.
- Application may depend on Domain and its own ports/contracts.
- Infrastructure implements Application/Domain contracts.
- HTTP layer may call Application use cases and format input/output only.
- HTTP Resources must not query Eloquent or call repositories.
- Application DTOs should be named `*Data`.
- HTTP FormRequests should be named `*Request`.
- Repository interfaces are ports defined in Domain or Application.
- Eloquent repository implementations belong to Infrastructure.
- Do not weaken Deptrac rules to hide violations.
- Do not add broad PHPStan/PHPMD ignore rules.

## Layer Structure

| Layer | Path | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Domain | `app/Domain` | Business logic, entities, value objects, domain services |
| Application | `app/Application` | Use cases, ports, DTOs, orchestration |
| Infrastructure | `app/Infrastructure` | Repository implementations, adapters, external services |
| HTTP | `app/Http` | Controllers, FormRequests, Resources, Middleware |
| Models | `app/Models` | Eloquent models (persistence only) |

